VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)\bDELETE\s+FROM\s+[^\s]+\s+WHERE\s+.*=.*\$.*
WHEN EXPR MISSING:%s|\?|:\w+|params=|execute\(
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects DELETE statements using user input directly without parameterization, increasing SQL injection risks.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for SQL Query: Direct DELETE with User Input.
